com.github.mrgoro.interactivedata.api.data.source

Class FileDataSource

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.mrgoro.interactivedata.api.data.source.StreamDataSource<java.lang.String>
      • com.github.mrgoro.interactivedata.api.data.source.FileDataSource
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DataSource

    public abstract class FileDataSource
extends StreamDataSource<java.lang.String>
    DataSource that uses a data file with separated values in each line. Generates DataObjects for each line. Mapping is used to associate values to their property names. To use the DataSource you have to extend this abstract class and override at least the method getPath() to specify the path of your file you want to use. A mapper is used to convert each line into a DataObject. The default mapping is derived from the first line of the file. The default separator to split the values of each line is ;. To adjust this behaviour override the methods getMappings() and getSeparator().
    Author:
    Philipp Schürmann

      • getMappings

        protected java.lang.String[] getMappings()
        Specifies the Mapping of columns inside the data file. The Mapping maps columns to properties in the data objects. The default mapping is derived from the first line of the file. The separator from getSeparator() is used. Example: 
         
      {@literal @}Override
      protected String[] getMapping() {
          return { "id", "name", "age" };
      }
        With the example mapping objects created form the data source have the properties id, name and age. Each line represents an object. Values in the first column are associated to the property id, values in the second column to the property name and values in the third column to the property age. When overriding the method note to adjust (override) the method skipLines() so that the first line is not skipped.
        Returns:
        Mapping of columns inside the data file as an String Array

      • getSeparator

        protected java.lang.String getSeparator()
